<description>Bo had a fantastic season for Bolton 
Wanderers in 2000-01. Although he had 
previously played as a centre forward, boss 
Sam Allardyce saw his potential in other 
areas and the hunch proved to be a 
masterstroke. Featuring mainly on the wings 
or just behind one or two other front-line 
strikers he was a revelation. Quick and 
skilful, with bags of pace and willing to 
chase every ball he swiftly become a real 
crowd favourite and will be aiming to retain 
his place as a regular in the line-up in 
2001-02.</description>

